text: Cameron Ross Cleeland (born August 15, 1975) is an American football tight end who last played for the St. Louis Rams of the NFL. Previously he had played for the New Orleans Saints and New England Patriots and went to the University of Washington. While a rookie with the Saints, he was struck in the eye by linebacker Andre Royal with a sock filled with coins during a hazing incident.Incognito feels ‘betrayed’ by Martin, by Mike Puma, November 9, 2013, New York Post Cleeland nearly lost his eye in addition to suffering a broken eye socket and broken nose.
